snippet.textDisplay: When I heard Bon Bon Chocolat I thought that the line distribution was fair and that this was going to be a great rookie group but now that I've seen this I realize how unfair it is. Yes Bon Bon Chocolat was their debut song but girls like Onda and Yiren almost gets no lines. Just simple words to repeat over and over again. While Mia gets a lot more lines and her own solo time on screen. But I don't hate Mia and I know that Mia isn't like this. It's their company who should maybe think that "Yes, as much as we all love Mia and as much as she is talented. We also have other girls that have amazing talents that don't get enough lines!" but no. I'm not blaming this on Mia at all. But this isn't fair for the others

snippet.textDisplay:
It's just a matter of time before the line distribution get more equal.
Right now, they are just a rookie group that is trying to establish themselves(and from the views, i would say they have), and so it would make more sense to give more lines to the more popular members.
Remember when (G)-Idle's Shuhua didnt get many lines now she is singing bridges and has been getting more attention each comeback.
Momo and sana from twice also, after mainly getting cute(1-2 second) sound bites in each song they slowly got more lines.
Red Velvet with Yeri, WJSN after Yeonjung joined also skewed the line distribution, but now they are focusing on other members.
There are probably countless examples, but these are just a few i managed to recall.
